. Latios and Latias are also based on birds, and due to Latias\'s {{DL|List of unused Pokémon and character designs|Blaziken / Latias|shared origin}} with {{p|Blaziken}}, they could be based on {{wp|junglefowl}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nLatias may derive from \'\'latere\'\' ({{wp|Latin}} for "to lie hidden"). \'\'As\'\' as a suffix may have been added to make it sound more feminine, opposite the more masculine-sounding \'\'os\'\' in {{p|Latios}}.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Dragon|type2=Psychic\n|ja=ラティアス \'\'Latias\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'latere\'\' (Latin for "to lie hidden") and \'\'As\'\' as a suffix for feminine\n|de=Latias|demeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|fr=Latias|frmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|es=Latias|esmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|it=Latias|itmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|ko=라티아스 \'\'Latias\'\'|komeaning=Transcription of its Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=拉帝亞斯 / 拉帝亚斯 \'\'Lādìyǎsī\'\' / \'\'Lādìyàsī\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name\n|zh_yue=拉帝亞斯 \'\'Lādai\'asī\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Same as Mandarin name\n|hi=लतियस \'\'Latias\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English/Japanese name\n|ru=Латиас \'\'Latias\'\'|rumeaning=Transliteration of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Latias (M05)]]\n* [[Eon duo (Adventures)]]\n* [[Eon duo]]\n<!--\n==Notes==-->\n\n==External links==\n*{{wp|Latias and Latios|Article on Wikipedia}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{Legendary Pokémon}}<br>\n{{Smash Bros.}}<br>\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Dragon|type2=Psychic}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Dragon|prevnum=379|prev=Registeel|nextnum=381|next=Latios}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Legendary Pokémon]]\n[[Category:Hoenn Legendary Pokémon]]\n[[Category:Roaming Pokémon]]\n[[Category:Pokémon with Mega Evolutions]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that appeared in the anime before their game debut]]\n[[Category:Purple-colored Pokémon]]<!--Mega Latias-->\n\n[[de:Latias]]\n[[es:Latias]]\n[[fr:Latias]]\n[[it:Latias]]\n[[ja:ラティアス]]\n[[zh